ENLIST
  Convert civilians into active military in a sector.

SYNTAX
  enlist <sects> <amount>
  enli   <sects> <amount>

DESCRIPTION
  Converts civilians into military troops in the specified sector(s).
  This happens immediately at no cost other than the civilians used.

  Rules:
    - Sector must be owned by you
    - Sector loyalty must be <= 70 (disloyal sectors refuse)
    - Per-sector limit: min(civ/2, 500, 999-current_mil)
    - At most half the sector's civilians can be drafted per command
    - Total across all sectors capped at 10,000 per call

  Military produced this way are ready immediately for orders,
  movement, and combat.  To free up troops back to civilian status,
  see 'info demobilize'.

EXAMPLE
  enlist 0,0 200            convert 200 civilians to military
  enlist * 50               enlist up to 50 per owned sector
  enlist 1,-3 400           enlist from the sector at rel (1,-3)

SEE ALSO
  demobilize  nation  census  sector-types
